main event: Two ellipsoid objects with blue-white exhaust and orange-reddish light were observed in Cincinnati, Ohio on December 13, 1955.
interesting points: The objects were observed for a total of 60 minutes with 45 minutes of visual observation and additional time using a telescope., The altitude of the objects was estimated to be 12,000 feet., The objects emitted a radiant orange translucent light., The sighting occurred over an overcast area and showed oscillating behavior., Insufficient data was concluded for further evaluation.
sighted object: two ellipsoid objects with blue-white exhaust and orange-reddish light
